From: Al-Nahari <nahari771735416@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:18:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] chore: force Next.js framework detection in Vercel

Vercel project settings had Output Directory overridden to 'dist'
(static-build builder), which doesn't apply to this Next.js app and
caused 'No Output Directory named dist found' after a successful
'next build'. Adding an explicit framework hint here as a safety net;
the Output Directory override in the Vercel dashboard should also be
cleared.
---
 vercel.json | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 vercel.json

diff --git a/vercel.json b/vercel.json
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..f92a3f8
--- /dev/null
+++ b/vercel.json
@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@
+{
+  "framework": "nextjs"
+}
-- 
2.43.0

